( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 18=

19
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:38,920
Leave?

20
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,630
You shouldn't have come back.

21
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:44,320
Just leave.

22
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,110
Leave right now.

23
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:49,160
All three of you, leave!

24
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,590
Never come back!

25
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,510
What else can you do besides running away?

26
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,480
Back then, at the slightest
sign of trouble,

27
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,320
you ran faster than anyone else.

28
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:03,160
You made it sound nice.

29
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:05,230
Roaming the world, completely free?

30
00:02:05,230 --> 00:02:06,480
You're just a coward!

31
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:08,790
Teaching opera singing?

32
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:10,880
A coward like you teaching Qinqiang opera,

33
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,390
can it still be called Qinqiang opera?

34
00:02:19,150 --> 00:02:20,390
That's Coward opera!

35
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:35,470
Master Gou.

36
00:02:41,230 --> 00:02:42,640
Did you watch tonight's

37
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:44,270
performance?

38
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:46,460
I did.

39
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:47,680
Know why it's a failure?

40
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:51,430
Pull hard, pull it up.

41
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,350
Pull it higher.

42
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:57,150
No skills off stage,

43
00:02:57,680 --> 00:02:59,040
nothing on stage.

44
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:09,680
I tied it myself.

45
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,400
The veil couldn't have pulled it down.

46
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,480
Mr. Gou.

47
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:15,760
I grew up being trained in modern opera.

48
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:17,920
I never had head binding before.

49
00:03:18,590 --> 00:03:20,310
You tied it too tight.

50
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:22,430
I couldn't take it.

51
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,790
If you can't take this little pain,

52
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:26,920
you shouldn't be in this profession.

53
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:28,840
Step aside!

54
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,590
Be careful!

55
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:04,520
You'll draw attention.

56
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:49,870
What are you doing here?

57
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,400
We're hungry.

58
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:54,360
Looking for some Mo to eat.

59
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,310
We'll leave right away.

60
00:04:57,580 --> 00:04:58,430
Don't grab me!

61
00:04:58,430 --> 00:04:59,270
Me first!

62
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,910
Let me out first. Me first!

63
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,150
The Mo issue is solved.

64
00:05:13,630 --> 00:05:14,470
Master Song.

65
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:16,180
Here.

66
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,080
Listen up.

67
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,150
The troupe's going to the countryside

68
00:05:19,150 --> 00:05:20,360
to perform Hong Hu Chi Wei Dui.

69
00:05:20,750 --> 00:05:22,870
- We're all going too.
- Give me more.

70
00:05:22,870 --> 00:05:23,840
Get prepared.

71
00:05:24,110 --> 00:05:24,960
All going?

72
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,310
They haven't done that play in years.

73
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:27,520
Why bring it back now?

74
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,560
Running out of options, huh?

75
00:05:28,910 --> 00:05:30,470
Bi Shang Liang Shan was a total flop.

76
00:05:30,470 --> 00:05:31,840
What else to perform?

77
00:05:32,710 --> 00:05:34,960
If a troupe doesn't perform, what is it?

78
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:37,080
They'll mess it up anyway.

79
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:38,960
What are you talking about?

80
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,270
Don't jinx it.

81
00:05:40,470 --> 00:05:42,590
You should have more hope.

82
00:06:21,580 --> 00:06:25,580
(Performing opera for the people)

83
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,460
(Theater in the country)

84
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:30,060
(Performing opera for the people)

85
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:33,830
Get off. Get off.

86
00:06:33,830 --> 00:06:34,750
- Okay.
- Hurry up.

87
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:36,040
Boys, help the girls out.

88
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,880
Come on.

89
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:37,720
Hurry up!

90
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,600
Come on. Be careful.

91
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:40,000
Unload the gear.

92
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:40,870
Hurry up.

93
00:06:40,870 --> 00:06:41,750
Line up now.

94
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,000
Start stage setup now.

95
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,950
Unload the gear. Stay safe.

96
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,520
Come on.

97
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:48,470
Okay, okay.

98
00:06:51,430 --> 00:06:52,560
Attention, everyone.

99
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,750
- Line up quickly.
- Attention.

100
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,620
Line up.

101
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:58,310
The kitchen is on the school playground.

102
00:06:58,310 --> 00:07:00,240
Food will be ready in an hour.

103
00:07:00,590 --> 00:07:01,430
Okay.

104
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,270
Qiu!

105
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:04,160
In an hour?

106
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,680
The water is too far from the kitchen.

107
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,190
Carrying water is exhausting us.

108
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:08,390
- How did you plan this?
- Okay, okay.

109
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,480
- I'll fix it now.
- Tell them to wait.

110
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,430
Hurry up.

111
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,160
I'll fix it right away.

112
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,040
Keep your spirits up.

113
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:14,920
Got it.

114
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,270
Master Song.

115
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,110
What?

116
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:24,830
Tell everyone it's two meals
a day tomorrow.

117
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:26,030
Why is that?

118
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,120
They eat at 10 AM tomorrow.

119
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:31,240
Tough show tonight. Let everyone sleep in.

120
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,040
They eat at 4 PM today.

121
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:35,070
They'll prep for the show after eating.

122
00:07:35,070 --> 00:07:36,680
You tell them. I don't
want to get yelled at.

123
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,950
I was invited to attend a banquet.

124
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:41,430
Unload the food. Hurry.

125
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:42,710
Bye.

126
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:44,120
So full of yourself.

127
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,160
Old fox.

128
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,480
I always have to play the bad guy.

129
00:07:48,160 --> 00:07:49,680
Only two meals?

130
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,240
The food budget won't last the month?

131
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,750
One meal is even better.

132
00:07:53,270 --> 00:07:54,240
Makes our job easier.

133
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,750
Back then,

134
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,510
they'd call me over from time to time

135
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,830
for meetings and studying.

136
00:08:03,310 --> 00:08:06,070
At least I had something real to do.

137
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:07,680
And now?

138
00:08:08,390 --> 00:08:09,240
Reform and Opening-up.

139
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,080
Times have changed.

140
00:08:11,310 --> 00:08:12,270
No more endless meetings.

141
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,070
I have plenty of free time.

142
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,000
I can't just do nothing.

143
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:18,310
So I opened this Xishi Tofu Shop.

144
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,680
Plus, I was recently made

145
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:25,390
Commune Cultural Station Director.

146
00:08:25,810 --> 00:08:26,680
Director?

147
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,390
How many people do you manage?

148
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:29,590
Just one.

149
00:08:30,100 --> 00:08:30,880
I

150
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:32,220
manage myself.

151
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:34,430
You make magic with tofu.

152
00:08:35,070 --> 00:08:37,070
We should bring Master Song here

153
00:08:37,070 --> 00:08:38,480
- to learn.
- Right.

154
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,680
He makes cabbage and tofu stew all day.

155
00:08:40,680 --> 00:08:41,530
Even pigs wouldn't eat it.

156
00:08:41,540 --> 00:08:42,390
Exactly.

157
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:45,040
If your troupe's food is terrible,

158
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,310
we can let it slide.

159
00:08:47,070 --> 00:08:50,120
But your troupe's plays are boring.

160
00:08:51,750 --> 00:08:53,510
That's unacceptable.

161
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,000
What era are we in?

162
00:08:58,870 --> 00:09:00,870
Why are you still performing those?

163
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,600
Passing off weeds as seeds

164
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,750
to fool us country folks?

165
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:07,920
Yeah, we're tired of them.

166
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,600
Right, fooling us farmers.

167
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,680
We don't want to fool you either.

168
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,310
Didn't Bi Shang Liang Shan fail?

169
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,830
We have no plays left.

170
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:21,310
You have great veteran artists.

171
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,150
Why don't you use them?

172
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:23,760
They did.

173
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,560
No use.

174
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:27,310
Did they use you or not?

175
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,070
There's a talent gap.

176
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,720
It's no use whoever comes.

177
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:33,640
Mr. Qin.

178
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,720
I came here to ask you

179
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:38,360
to write a modern play for us.

180
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:43,160
If you asked me to make tofu for you,

181
00:09:43,270 --> 00:09:44,110
I could do that.

182
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:46,310
But the modern play...

183
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,310
I haven't written anything in years.

184
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:49,180
With your skills...

185
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:51,270
How is Hu Sanyuan? Any news on him?

186
00:09:51,950 --> 00:09:52,800
No news.

187
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,270
He won't be out for at least a year.

188
00:09:54,270 --> 00:09:55,110
That's not important.

189
00:09:55,270 --> 00:09:56,310
What's important is

190
00:09:56,310 --> 00:09:59,070
that we urgently need a modern play.

191
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:01,960
Right.

192
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,120
The tofu is delicious.

193
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:05,390
You like the tofu?

194
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:06,510
I'll send you two loads tomorrow.

195
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:07,080
Great.

196
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:10,340
(Fourth Qinchuan Provincial
Prison System Art Showcase)

197
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:14,670
Next, Beishan Prison's
Rebirth Propaganda Team.

198
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:18,120
Performing Qinqiang opera Zhan Shan Tong.

199
00:10:19,150 --> 00:10:20,440
Quick time, march.

200
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,320
One, two, one.

201
00:10:22,670 --> 00:10:24,080
One, two, one.

202
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,790
One, two, one.

203
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:27,870
Sit.

204
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:53,790
♪With a loud shout♪

205
00:10:56,480 --> 00:11:05,720
♪Tied outside the tent♪

206
00:11:21,340 --> 00:11:24,620
(Rhythm and Arts Showcase)

207
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,080
Laidi.

208
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,200
How are you doing?

209
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:48,840
Doing great.

210
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,720
Any news about your uncle?

211
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,160
None.

212
00:12:54,790 --> 00:12:56,720
I wonder how he's been
these past few years.

213
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:00,750
I used to dream about him a lot.

214
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,360
Haven't dreamed of him lately.

215
00:13:03,790 --> 00:13:05,360
Any news about Hua Caixiang?

216
00:13:05,870 --> 00:13:06,870
None either.

217
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:09,790
I heard she's had a hard time lately.

218
00:13:10,360 --> 00:13:11,630
When they were in the troupe,

219
00:13:11,630 --> 00:13:13,120
I didn't really notice it.

220
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,960
Now that they've left the troupe,

221
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:16,960
it's gotten so boring.

222
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,630
I remember this area

223
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,270
is near your hometown, right?

224
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:27,150
When was the last time you went back?

225
00:13:27,320 --> 00:13:28,360
A few years ago.

226
00:13:29,670 --> 00:13:31,000
Ever since Ms. Hua and I

227
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:33,000
brought you out of your hometown,

228
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:34,630
you've never gone back?

229
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,550
You must miss home a lot.

230
00:13:41,790 --> 00:13:42,630
Listen.

231
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:43,720
After the performance,

232
00:13:44,270 --> 00:13:45,390
I'll go back with you.

233
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:48,510
It's a half-day trek home from here.

234
00:13:48,510 --> 00:13:50,390
A round trip takes a whole day.

235
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,120
We're short-staffed. I can't leave.

236
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,000
Is something on your mind?

237
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:57,590
No.

238
00:13:59,670 --> 00:14:01,790
If you need anything or have any issues,

239
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:03,510
you must let me know.

240
00:15:02,510 --> 00:15:03,550
That's right. Careful.

241
00:15:03,550 --> 00:15:04,870
Straighten that curtain out.

242
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:05,960
Zhu.

243
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,000
Right, tighten it.

244
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,240
Make sure the rope is tight.

245
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,480
- Zhu.
- Right. Careful.

246
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,640
Tighten it.

247
00:15:12,670 --> 00:15:13,510
Zhu.

248
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,750
Zhu, let's go.

249
00:15:15,510 --> 00:15:16,510
Go? Go where?

250
00:15:16,510 --> 00:15:17,350
Come with me.

251
00:15:17,400 --> 00:15:18,240
What is it?

252
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,080
I'm busy here.

253
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,080
Just come.

254
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,030
Come on.

255
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:22,440
- Go where?
- Follow me.

256
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,280
You'll know.

257
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:25,080
Why so mysterious?

258
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,630
Her. That kid.

259
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:28,510
An actress in your troupe?

260
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:31,150
What actress?

261
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:32,910
She's a kitchen maid.

262
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,960
Are you kidding?

263
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:35,810
This...

264
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:38,510
Such great skills! She's a good Wudan!

265
00:15:40,510 --> 00:15:42,510
The kitchen maid of Tianbo Yang Mansion!

266
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:43,600
That's right!

267
00:15:44,150 --> 00:15:46,480
What Tianbo Yang Mansion?

268
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,550
Hu Sanyuan's niece!

269
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:51,390
Gou Cunzhong's apprentice.

270
00:15:52,340 --> 00:15:53,680
Hu Sanyuan's niece?

271
00:15:54,870 --> 00:15:57,270
The one who rushed to eat four of my Mo

272
00:15:57,270 --> 00:15:58,670
and almost choked to death?

273
00:15:58,750 --> 00:15:59,590
Exactly.

274
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:00,840
She doesn't look like her.

275
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:02,750
How old was she?

276
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:04,030
How old is she now?

277
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,030
Girls change as they grow up!

278
00:16:06,270 --> 00:16:07,480
If she were in our troupe,

279
00:16:07,910 --> 00:16:09,390
she'd be even more beautiful.

280
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,910
Who left the tofu here?

281
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:13,150
Me.

282
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:14,790
I delivered the tofu.

283
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,550
Kid, remember this.

284
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,270
My name is Qin Bawa.

285
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:20,000
A playwright.

286
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:24,480
(Xishi Tofu Shop)
Besides Da Jiao Zan?

287
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,240
We only taught her that opera excerpt.

288
00:16:28,980 --> 00:16:29,840
Then, for tonight,

289
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:31,440
can we add that excerpt?

290
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,390
The leaders won't agree.

291
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:39,510
Didn't I explain the situation?

292
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:40,590
What situation?

293
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:41,720
We're not allowed to

294
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:42,910
rehearse Yang Pai Feng.

295
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:45,960
It is ridiculous.

296
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,240
Just Troupe Leader Huang

297
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:48,510
shouting slogans.

298
00:16:48,510 --> 00:16:49,750
And you get scared.

299
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,320
Are his words gospel?

300
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:53,910
You don't know about our troupe.

301
00:16:54,270 --> 00:16:55,630
I may not know the situation.

302
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:57,630
But I know you, Zhu Jiru.

303
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,200
Just tell me, yes or no?

304
00:17:01,790 --> 00:17:02,720
Straighten up.

305
00:17:02,910 --> 00:17:03,750
Learn from me.

306
00:17:04,360 --> 00:17:05,870
Live with some backbone, okay?

307
00:17:08,030 --> 00:17:10,840
What can one tough Zhu Jiru do?

308
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:13,600
You can change that kid's fate!

309
00:17:14,320 --> 00:17:16,270
People are eating here, Bawa.

310
00:17:16,550 --> 00:17:18,120
Calm down. Talk nicely.

311
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,080
Go.

312
00:17:19,630 --> 00:17:20,510
Just go.

313
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:22,600
Nothing.

314
00:17:22,630 --> 00:17:23,600
- I'm telling you, Zhu Jiru.
- Just eat.

315
00:17:24,120 --> 00:17:26,790
If you watch Huang Zhengjing ruin the kid,

316
00:17:26,870 --> 00:17:27,790
and you say nothing,

317
00:17:28,910 --> 00:17:30,550
you're an accomplice.

318
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:33,600
Can't we eat in peace?

319
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,030
Shut up and eat your food!

320
00:17:36,550 --> 00:17:38,080
Stop blowing things out of proportion!

321
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:39,080
- Sorry.
- You have no right!

322
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:39,920
This dish is free.

323
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,390
- Look, look!
- Enjoy.

324
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:43,390
He slammed the table and yelled.

325
00:17:43,390 --> 00:17:44,630
He spilled my tea.

326
00:17:44,790 --> 00:17:47,240
I've been talking to him calmly.

327
00:17:47,320 --> 00:17:48,390
Watch your tone.

328
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:52,840
Tough now?

329
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,080
Feeling bold now?

330
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,790
Why are you talking to me so tough?

331
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,870
Is it because I have no power?

332
00:18:03,390 --> 00:18:05,200
Just a solemn reminder

333
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:07,910
that I'm the Cultural Station Director.

334
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:09,630
Your troupe's performance fee

335
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,270
is paid by the Station.

336
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:12,880
You listen,

337
00:18:12,910 --> 00:18:14,150
no Da Jiao Zan today,

338
00:18:14,910 --> 00:18:17,750
then no payment from the Station.

339
00:18:18,200 --> 00:18:20,910
I keep my word.

340
00:18:21,440 --> 00:18:22,280
So?

341
00:18:23,910 --> 00:18:26,270
Meng Liang and Jiao Zan are in town.

342
00:18:26,630 --> 00:18:27,960
We don't have the costumes.

343
00:18:28,270 --> 00:18:29,270
We do.

344
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:31,510
Those old things

345
00:18:31,510 --> 00:18:33,480
were kept safe by us old folks.

346
00:18:33,960 --> 00:18:35,510
We even performed for you.

347
00:18:35,510 --> 00:18:36,600
How could you forget?

348
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:37,630
And the drums?

349
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:39,000
Can He Dachui play?

350
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:41,310
He played Bi Shang Liang Shan.

351
00:18:41,830 --> 00:18:44,480
The kid and I will run it twice with music.

352
00:18:44,960 --> 00:18:46,030
It shouldn't be a problem.

353
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:47,590
You would think!

354
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,640
Will he play for you?

355
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:52,200
Let's go talk to him.

356
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:55,510
His drumming isn't good,

357
00:18:55,510 --> 00:18:56,960
and neither is his temper.

358
00:18:56,960 --> 00:18:58,510
Master Qiu, keep your temper

359
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:00,030
- in check later.
- I know.

360
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,310
Watch your tone.

361
00:19:01,870 --> 00:19:02,750
You're asking for a favor.

362
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,350
- Hello, Troupe Leader Zhu.
- Hello.

363
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:05,940
Okay.

364
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:07,790
I'll talk to him about our show first.

365
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:08,630
Okay.

366
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:10,390
He Dachui.

367
00:19:11,640 --> 00:19:13,070
I need to discuss something with you.

368
00:19:13,070 --> 00:19:13,910
Go ahead.

369
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,000
Tonight, I want to

370
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,270
add an opera excerpt.

371
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:17,430
What is it?

372
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:18,800
Da Jiao Zan.

373
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:20,640
Da Jiao Zan?

374
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,960
- Yang...
- The excerpt from Yang Pai Feng.

375
00:19:23,350 --> 00:19:25,310
It's an old play. No one can sing it.

376
00:19:25,720 --> 00:19:27,350
Yi Qing'e can.

377
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,790
- Who?
- Yi Qing'e.

378
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:32,400
The kitchen maid playing a kitchen maid.

379
00:19:33,590 --> 00:19:34,720
Hu Sanyuan's niece?

380
00:19:34,720 --> 00:19:35,560
Exactly.

381
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,720
Total nonsense.

382
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:38,280
No way. That kid can't sing.

383
00:19:39,200 --> 00:19:40,590
I've seen her skills.

384
00:19:40,590 --> 00:19:41,510
Really good.

385
00:19:42,070 --> 00:19:43,160
Good my foot.

386
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:44,680
I believe she stokes fires well.

387
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:46,400
I believe she chops veggies well.

388
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:48,030
If you say she outcooks Master Song,

389
00:19:48,030 --> 00:19:49,310
I'd be half-convinced.

390
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:50,590
She sings opera well?

391
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,030
I wouldn't believe it to save my life.

392
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,550
Hey, that one! That one.

393
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,350
A secret for you.

394
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,350
Gou Cunzhong took her as an apprentice

395
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:00,310
many years ago.

396
00:20:00,310 --> 00:20:01,310
She's been training for years too.

397
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,440
- Who?
- Gou Cunzhong.

398
00:20:03,960 --> 00:20:05,030
I don't trust him!

399
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:07,030
In Bi Shang Liang Shan,

400
00:20:07,030 --> 00:20:08,640
Hu Sanniang sang so terribly.

401
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,110
I won't play. I just can't.

402
00:20:10,110 --> 00:20:11,440
- Let me.
- Stay out of it.

403
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:12,480
- Come on.
- Stay out of it.

404
00:20:12,480 --> 00:20:13,320
Dachui.

405
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:15,310
This play is an easy gig.

406
00:20:15,310 --> 00:20:16,790
The opening,

407
00:20:16,790 --> 00:20:17,830
Shua Hai Er,

408
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:19,920
and the finale. All right?

409
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,720
You even played for Bi Shang Liang Shan.

410
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,480
And the whole troupe thinks

411
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:25,920
you're playing better and better.

412
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:28,070
This play is a piece of cake for you.

413
00:20:28,070 --> 00:20:29,000
Come on.

414
00:20:30,090 --> 00:20:30,940
Dachui.

415
00:20:30,960 --> 00:20:33,070
Stop flattering me like that.

416
00:20:33,070 --> 00:20:34,310
Last time in Bi Shang Liang Shan,

417
00:20:34,310 --> 00:20:36,200
you guys almost ruined me.

418
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,680
The band and actors need to sync up.

419
00:20:39,030 --> 00:20:40,160
Just leave it alone.

420
00:20:40,160 --> 00:20:41,510
It'll take at least half a month.

421
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:44,070
If you're not embarrassed, I am.

422
00:20:44,440 --> 00:20:46,510
No, here's the thing.

423
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:48,400
This morning, a Commune official

424
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,550
was strolling around here.

425
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:52,070
He happened to see Qing'e practicing.

426
00:20:52,070 --> 00:20:53,960
And he happens to be an expert.

427
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:56,310
He was blown away by her skills.

428
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,350
He insists on adding the show.

429
00:20:58,920 --> 00:20:59,960
If we don't add it,

430
00:21:00,310 --> 00:21:02,480
the troupe won't get a single penny.

431
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,550
What can we do?

432
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:05,590
What does that have to do with me?

433
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,030
Hang it at position four.

434
00:21:09,550 --> 00:21:10,550
Right, position four.

435
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:15,480
Dachui.

436
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:18,750
Let her do a run-through, and take a look.

437
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,350
Watch it first before deciding.

438
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:22,870
Just watching?

439
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:26,400
Stop, stop, stop!

440
00:21:27,030 --> 00:21:28,640
Come on, kitchen meeting.

441
00:21:28,640 --> 00:21:30,550
Can't see we're so busy?

442
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:32,880
Our kitchen is gonna get celebrated!

443
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,830
I'd just be happy

444
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:35,070
not to get yelled at.

445
00:21:35,750 --> 00:21:36,590
Guess.

446
00:21:36,790 --> 00:21:38,110
No. Just tell us!

447
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,960
Tonight, our kitchen is gonna

448
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,790
play the lead!

449
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:43,200
What do you mean?

450
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:45,830
Zhu Jiru and the Commune leaders just agreed

451
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,960
to add a show tonight, Da Jiao Zan.

452
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:51,350
Yi Qing'e takes the lead!

453
00:21:53,030 --> 00:21:54,440
That's wonderful!

454
00:21:54,440 --> 00:21:56,310
I called two helpers. They'll be here soon.

455
00:21:56,310 --> 00:21:57,560
- Okay.
- Free the kid up.

456
00:21:57,750 --> 00:21:58,750
Let her get ready.

457
00:21:58,750 --> 00:21:59,590
Sure.

458
00:22:01,030 --> 00:22:01,870
Kid.

459
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,270
I already made the call.

460
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,510
Your three masters bring the costumes.

461
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,640
Let's do a run-through
before they arrive.

462
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,790
Why so suddenly?

463
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,000
Not at all!

464
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,480
Hard work pays off!

465
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,440
I knew it!

466
00:22:15,440 --> 00:22:17,440
Our kid will make it eventually!

467
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:19,830
Laidi, get up.

468
00:22:19,830 --> 00:22:20,720
Stop working.

469
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:22,070
Let's go wash your face.

470
00:22:22,070 --> 00:22:23,480
Get ready for the run-through.

471
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,320
Nice and clean.

472
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:25,500
Hey, ignore her.

473
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:26,350
Come here.

474
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:27,240
Let's discuss something.

475
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,750
- What is it?
- Just come here.

476
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,830
Any other good news?

477
00:22:30,830 --> 00:22:31,720
Chop your veggies.

478
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,480
Go wash your face.

479
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,110
What's wrong?

480
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,240
I'm nervous.

481
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:51,240
I'm nervous.

482
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:55,880
Don't be afraid, kid.

483
00:22:57,790 --> 00:22:59,830
Anyone would be nervous.

484
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:02,030
Like a bride on her wedding day,

485
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,550
there's a first time for everything.

486
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,240
Listen to me.

487
00:23:06,590 --> 00:23:08,920
Just sing how you usually practice.

488
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,000
You'll be absolutely fine.

489
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:16,880
The kid might not sing.

490
00:23:17,590 --> 00:23:19,790
First you say yes, then you say no.

491
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,400
Will the kid sing or not?

492
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:23,070
If it's a no,

493
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,640
it is because He Dachui

494
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,200
won't play the drums for her.

495
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,320
Why?

496
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:28,720
No idea.

497
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:33,310
I think He Dachui doubts the kid can sing.

498
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:36,000
So, can the kid sing or not?

499
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,510
It's not about whether she can.

500
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:41,750
If she gets on stage today,

501
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:44,070
she might never step down.

502
00:23:45,270 --> 00:23:47,310
The lead in our troupe...

503
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:48,790
Hua Caixiang.

504
00:23:49,310 --> 00:23:50,270
Mi Lan.

505
00:23:50,830 --> 00:23:52,830
Every single one of them.

506
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:54,510
I guarantee it

507
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,040
from now on,

508
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:59,110
no one can fight her for the lead.

509
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,880
Isn't that a good thing?

510
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:07,070
Like heck it is.

511
00:24:07,070 --> 00:24:08,590
What do you mean?

512
00:24:09,830 --> 00:24:11,790
What's wrong? Just tell me.

513
00:24:14,310 --> 00:24:15,920
Go talk to He Dachui.

514
00:24:17,510 --> 00:24:18,350
Why me?

515
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:20,400
Because he listens to you.

516
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:22,830
What do you mean?

517
00:24:34,110 --> 00:24:35,070
She didn't even gasp.

518
00:24:35,350 --> 00:24:37,110
You, either.

519
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:38,840
Good?

520
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,160
Good or bad,

521
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,310
it's not up to me.

522
00:24:41,790 --> 00:24:42,750
Then whom?

523
00:25:00,160 --> 00:25:01,440
She dared to hit him.

524
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,790
You'll know when you grow up.

525
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:06,030
Men are very easy to handle.

526
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:47,510
The kid's head got hit.

527
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:53,480
Not bad.

528
00:25:54,200 --> 00:25:55,310
Hurry up and cook.

529
00:25:55,550 --> 00:25:56,480
Keep it up.

530
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:06,800
Mo.

531
00:26:06,930 --> 00:26:07,790
Mo.

532
00:26:07,790 --> 00:26:09,310
What's on your mind?

533
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:10,560
Alright, okay.

534
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,680
Attention, everyone.

535
00:26:16,070 --> 00:26:18,510
Hurry up and eat, get ready.

536
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:19,920
We go in at 5:30.

537
00:26:19,920 --> 00:26:21,510
The show starts at 6:00 sharp.

538
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:24,790
- Okay, okay.
- Okay.

539
00:26:25,440 --> 00:26:27,070
Where are the band guys?

540
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:29,510
Eat. No need to worry about it.

541
00:26:30,030 --> 00:26:31,270
Sing a cappella?

542
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:46,510
That's about enough.

543
00:26:46,510 --> 00:26:47,510
We're going to eat.

544
00:26:47,880 --> 00:26:48,920
Thank you. Thanks, everyone.

545
00:26:49,200 --> 00:26:50,310
Hurry. Go eat.

546
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:52,440
When will your sidekicks get here?

547
00:26:52,440 --> 00:26:53,280
Soon.

548
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:22,550
Master Gou!

549
00:27:28,110 --> 00:27:29,960
You and your three ancient relics

550
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:30,880
better get ready.

551
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:32,040
See you on stage.

552
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:37,640
I'm relieved you're here.

553
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,320
Look at me.

554
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,590
Remember today,

555
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:43,110
the day of your debut.

556
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:47,750
Great! You are finally here! Great!

557
00:27:48,550 --> 00:27:49,720
Me, the kid, and the band.

558
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:51,550
We ran through it twice.

559
00:27:52,070 --> 00:27:53,920
Go wash your faces and eat.

560
00:27:53,920 --> 00:27:55,440
Then do the kid's makeup.

561
00:27:55,920 --> 00:27:57,360
- This way. Come.
- Okay.

562
00:27:57,480 --> 00:27:58,550
This way.

563
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:00,510
- Let's go.
- Laidi. Laidi!

564
00:28:00,510 --> 00:28:01,720
- Quick, quick!
- Come with me.

565
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:02,560
What is it?

566
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:03,830
Don't worry about it.

567
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:06,270
No eating! Head binding is up next!

568
00:28:06,270 --> 00:28:07,670
- You're so fussy.
- This way.

569
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:15,480
Today,

570
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,750
you are marrying the stage.

571
00:28:20,270 --> 00:28:22,510
The kitchen is your maternal home.

572
00:28:25,070 --> 00:28:26,350
And I am your mother.

573
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:34,110
You must be washed spotless

574
00:28:34,590 --> 00:28:36,030
before going on stage.

575
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:54,140
Reporting, Hu Sanyuan is here.

576
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:55,040
Come in.

577
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:55,900
Go in.

578
00:28:58,550 --> 00:29:00,030
The competition results are out.

579
00:29:01,070 --> 00:29:02,310
We came up empty.

580
00:29:02,790 --> 00:29:03,960
And got slapped with a label.

581
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:05,960
I don't get what you mean.

582
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:11,590
First, second, and third prizes.

583
00:29:11,590 --> 00:29:13,160
Encouragement and hope prizes.

584
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:16,680
All Prison Propaganda Teams won,

585
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,520
except us.

586
00:29:20,750 --> 00:29:22,030
What label did we get?

587
00:29:23,460 --> 00:29:24,940
(Our track chosen for the event was unfit.)

588
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:27,790
But why?

589
00:29:29,270 --> 00:29:30,110
Why?

590
00:29:30,790 --> 00:29:33,960
"Executioners, escort the lord here now."

591
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:36,110
"Waiting at the execution ground."

592
00:29:36,920 --> 00:29:37,920
Then someone asked.

593
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:42,640
"Who are the executioners?
Who is the lord?"

594
00:29:44,110 --> 00:29:46,680
"Are you mocking someone indirectly?"

595
00:29:46,960 --> 00:29:48,000
They needed me to explain.

596
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:50,550
We're singing an old opera.

597
00:29:50,550 --> 00:29:53,110
It's about chaos in the
Sui and Tang Dynasties.

598
00:29:53,110 --> 00:29:53,950
How...

599
00:29:54,510 --> 00:29:55,750
No need to explain to me.

600
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:58,720
What I told them was exactly

601
00:29:58,720 --> 00:29:59,560
what you said.

602
00:30:03,070 --> 00:30:04,880
Sir, lock me up then.

603
00:30:06,030 --> 00:30:07,440
How come it's your fault?

604
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,200
I told you to sing.

605
00:30:10,790 --> 00:30:13,240
What's wrong with these people?

606
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,310
It's the Reform and Opening-up era.

607
00:30:15,790 --> 00:30:18,000
Some people's bodies have moved on,

608
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,750
but their minds are stuck in the past.

609
00:30:20,510 --> 00:30:21,550
In my heart,

610
00:30:21,960 --> 00:30:22,960
our performance

611
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:24,830
deserves the grand prize.

612
00:30:35,070 --> 00:30:44,680
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)
♪Honghu waters, wave upon wave♪

613
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:53,110
♪The shores of Honghu are my home♪

614
00:30:53,750 --> 00:30:58,030
♪Boats set out at dawn
to cast their nets♪

615
00:30:58,030 --> 00:31:02,270
♪Returning in the evening
with holds full of fish♪

616
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:16,240
♪Returning in the evening
with holds full of fish♪

617
00:32:01,550 --> 00:32:02,390
Now,

618
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:03,640
press your ears down.

619
00:32:18,790 --> 00:32:19,790
Bear with it.

620
00:32:23,200 --> 00:32:24,200
It hurts.

621
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:26,830
Loosen it a bit.

622
00:32:26,830 --> 00:32:29,070
It's too tight. She can't take it.

623
00:32:29,070 --> 00:32:30,160
She has to.

624
00:32:30,640 --> 00:32:32,680
If she passes out, how can she perform?

625
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:33,920
Shut up.

626
00:32:35,790 --> 00:32:37,270
Head binding is your first test.

627
00:32:38,070 --> 00:32:40,270
You must suffer this to sing opera.

628
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:43,720
Now,

629
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:44,830
get up and walk.

630
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:47,550
Now Yi Qing'e finally understood

631
00:32:47,550 --> 00:32:50,350
why Mi Lan was in unbearable pain.

632
00:32:50,720 --> 00:32:54,200
Head binding is cruelest for a Dan role.

633
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:57,920
It's like torturing the head.

634
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:00,160
It's too tight. Loosen it.

635
00:33:00,160 --> 00:33:01,720
Shut your trap!

636
00:33:08,790 --> 00:33:09,640
How is it going?

637
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:10,720
Almost done.

638
00:33:11,270 --> 00:33:12,680
They're almost done.

639
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:14,640
How much longer?

640
00:33:16,070 --> 00:33:16,910
How's the band?

641
00:33:17,350 --> 00:33:19,160
We're lucky if they play it all.

642
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,640
Don't expect too much.

643
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:21,550
Hurry up.

644
00:33:21,550 --> 00:33:22,510
Okay, right away.

645
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:24,190
Is it okay?

646
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,960
♪As long as we face
the sun like sunflowers♪

647
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:27,960
♪Holding high♪

648
00:33:27,960 --> 00:33:29,920
♪The red flag raised in Jinggangshan♪

649
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:31,030
Hurry, hurry up!

650
00:33:31,520 --> 00:33:34,400
♪March towards victory♪

651
00:33:41,380 --> 00:33:46,460
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

652
00:34:12,070 --> 00:34:13,110
On stage,

653
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,160
Master Zhou and Master Qiu will guide you.

654
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:19,480
They'll set the rhythm for you.

655
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:22,200
Just follow their rhythm.

656
00:34:33,830 --> 00:34:35,790
Don't follow the rhythm of the drums.

657
00:34:36,750 --> 00:34:38,720
Stick to the rhythm I teach you.

658
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:40,640
Let the drums follow you.

659
00:35:07,070 --> 00:35:08,160
Don't look at me.

660
00:35:09,110 --> 00:35:10,270
Look at the audience.

661
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,640
What do you see?

662
00:35:21,310 --> 00:35:22,240
People.

663
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:26,270
Look up at the sky.

664
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,210
What do you see?

665
00:35:36,310 --> 00:35:38,200
Stars.

666
00:35:41,750 --> 00:35:43,680
The highest state of acting

667
00:35:45,030 --> 00:35:46,320
is not performing for people,

668
00:35:48,110 --> 00:35:49,920
but performing for Heaven.

669
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,280
Forget the audience.

670
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:56,280
Got it?

671
00:35:57,960 --> 00:35:59,070
Got it.

